  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study compares two groups of patients undergoing a gynecological surgey under general
      anesthesia: one group in which intraoperative analgesia is guided by the
      Analgesia-nociception index, and another group in which intraoperative analgesia is managed
      as in standard practice. The objective is to assess if the Analgesia Nociception Index may
      result in a decrease in total analgesic drugs consumption, a decrease in post-operative pain
      and in chronic pain development.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
